This class represents a customer in the
Travel Australia Booking System.

This class is used to store customer details
such as customer name and contact number.

Features:
- Stores customer information
- Displays customer details
- Supports constructor overloading
*/

public class Customer {
	
	//instance variables
	// stores customer name
	private String customerName;
	
	// stores customer contact number
	private String contactNumber;

	//constructor Used to create a customer object with name and contact number
	public Customer(String customerName, String contactNumber) {
		this.customerName=customerName;
		this.contactNumber=contactNumber;
	}
	
	
	//Overloaded constructor Used when only customer name is provided
	public Customer(String customerName) {

	    this.customerName = customerName;
	    this.contactNumber = "Not Provided";

	}
	
	//getters
	public String getCustomerName() {
		return customerName;
	}
	
	public String getContactNumber() {
		return contactNumber;
	}
	
	public void displayCustomer() {
		System.out.println("Customer Name: " + customerName);
		System.out.println("Contact Number: " + contactNumber);
	}


}
